.SH "NAME"
pci_get_class \- begin or continue searching for a PCI device by class
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'struct\ pci_dev\ *\ pci_get_class('u
.BI "struct pci_dev * pci_get_class(unsigned\ int\ " "class" ", struct\ pci_dev\ *\ " "from" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIclass\fR
.RS 4
search for a PCI device with this class designation
.RE
.PP
\fIfrom\fR
.RS 4
Previous PCI device found in search, or
\fBNULL\fR
for new search\&.
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Iterates through the list of known PCI devices\&. If a PCI device is found with a matching
\fIclass\fR, the reference count to the device is incremented and a pointer to its device structure is returned\&. Otherwise,
\fBNULL\fR
is returned\&. A new search is initiated by passing
\fBNULL\fR
as the
\fIfrom\fR
argument\&. Otherwise if
\fIfrom\fR
is not
\fBNULL\fR, searches continue from next device on the global list\&. The reference count for
\fIfrom\fR
is always decremented if it is not
\fBNULL\fR\&.
